<p>The model was not failing at the task. We just were not operating from the same reality yet.</p>

<p>That is the layer I keep coming back to.</p>

<h2 id="none-of-that-was-the-task">None of that was the task</h2>

<p>The task was simple: update image references.</p>

<p>What actually happened was something else:</p>

<ul>
  <li>checking assumptions</li>
  <li>correcting structure</li>
  <li>aligning on what exists</li>
</ul>

<p>Small things.</p>

<p>But they stack.</p>

<h2 id="the-model-wasnt-failing">The model wasn‚Äôt failing</h2>

<p>Let‚Äôs be clear.</p>

<p>It did what I asked.<br />
It adapted.<br />
It kept going.</p>

